.TH "nd_pfn_validate" 9 "nd_pfn_validate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nd_pfn_validate \- read and validate info-block
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nd_pfn_validate
.BI "(struct nd_pfn *nd_pfn "  ","
.BI "const char *sig "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "nd_pfn" 12
fsdax namespace runtime state / properties
.IP "sig" 12
'devdax' or 'fsdax' signature
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Upon return the info-block buffer contents (->pfn_sb) are
indeterminate when validation fails, and a coherent info-block
otherwise.
